fields.about:
I'm a professor of computer science in Course 6, and I regularly teach 6.005 Software Construction and [6.813/6.831 User Interface Design and Implementation](courses.csail.mit.edu/6.831).

As a Course 6 undergrad, I took 6.001 with Gerry Sussman and Peter Szolovits, 6.170 with Barbara Liskov and Frans Kaashoek, 6.035, and 6.821 with David Gifford.

Our 6.170 project was Ataxx, a kind of Othello.

These days I do research on crowdsourcing and HCI for software development.

fields.about:
I write/support electronic design tools  for Intel CPU design. I've been doing this for almost 20 years and it's been a very enjoyable job.

In my free time, I enjoy photography, woodworking, and over the last couple years, I built a working CNC wood router.

fields.about: [6.005](http://stellar.mit.edu/S/course/6/sp13/6.005/index.html) covers principles of software engineering, including specifications, abstract data types, testing, design patterns, and map/filter/reduce.  Students need help with improving their coding style and clarity.  Last semester's [problem sets](http://stellar.mit.edu/S/course/6/fa12/6.005/materials.html) and [code reviewing instructions](http://stellar.mit.edu/S/course/6/fa12/6.005/courseMaterial/topics/topic1/resource/text/text) will give you an idea of what's involved.  The process is online reviewing by commenting on Java source code.
